modules.description: Calculates the base-2 logarithm of the branching factor for a given tree structure. It operates on integer values representing node degrees in hierarchical data. Used to determine the minimum height of a balanced tree for a specified number of children per node.

provides efficient indexed access and modification of immutable sequences, supporting operations such as updating elements at specific positions and retrieving values by index. It works with persistent vector data structures that maintain historical versions after modifications. Use cases include implementing versioned data structures or immutable state transitions in applications requiring efficient random access.

Provides efficient, persistent vector operations using a bitwise trie structure. Supports logarithmic time complexity for indexing and updating elements, with operations tailored for hierarchical data. Key data types include persistent vectors and node degree representations, enabling tasks like calculating tree heights and managing balanced structures. Examples include building immutable sequences with efficient updates and analyzing tree depth based on branching factors.
